Drop rate on these shards is reported to be about 1%, they seem to have an equal chance of dropping off any mob in the zone. They *are* No-Drop.  Eormid said this about skyfire mobs: avoid chromodracs cause they have debuffs. Just pull the weaker stuff if possible. Drakes are immune to stuns. I also did shouts/auctions for looting rights - think I got one or two that way in addition to what my group killed - most times there are just folks soloing there for spells so the shard is useless...<br>
Sulissa says: They're not too bad if you hold the area around the entrance of VP ...not all that bad meaning 2 or 3 days worth of camping /rude shards.<br>
<br>
Also I find them referred to as fragments...<br>
